  "summary": "## Summary: Mobile Device Optimization with Bottom Navigation\n\n### Changes Implemented\n- **Mobile bottom navigation bar**: Created a new `MobileBottomNav` component with 4 core tabs (Brain, Inbox, Meetings, Calendar) and a \"More\" button that opens a drawer with access to all other pages (Dashboard, Kanban, Decisions, Reviews, Pages, Contacts, Analytics, Integrations, AI Prompts, Extensions)\n- **Responsive AppShell layout**: Desktop sidebar is hidden on mobile (`md:` breakpoint); mobile bottom nav appears instead; main content has bottom padding to avoid overlap with the bottom nav\n- **Viewport metadata**: Added proper `viewport` export with `device-width`, `initialScale`, and responsive `themeColor` for light/dark mode; added `appleWebApp` metadata for PWA support\n- **Brain chat mobile optimization**: Session sidebar becomes a slide-out overlay on mobile (with backdrop) instead of a fixed sidebar; auto-detects mobile viewport and hides sidebar by default; chat messages, input area, and knowledge tab all use responsive padding and spacing\n- **ThoughtDetailDrawer**: Full-width on mobile (`w-full`) instead of fixed `400px`, with desktop breakpoint fallback (`md:w-[400px]`)\n- **Touch feedback**: Added `active:scale-95 active:opacity-70` to bottom nav tab buttons for press feedback\n- **Mobile CSS utilities**: Added mobile-specific styles including horizontal overflow prevention, hidden scrollbars, and smooth touch scrolling\n- **Accessibility**: Kept viewport zoomable (no `userScalable: false`) for WCAG compliance\n\n### Files Modified\n- `app/layout.tsx` — Added `Viewport` export with theme colors and `appleWebApp` metadata\n- `components/ui/AppShell.tsx` — Restructured to hide SideNav on mobile, show MobileBottomNav, add responsive content padding\n- `components/ui/MobileBottomNav.tsx` — **New file** — Bottom tab bar with 4 primary tabs + More drawer\n- `app/(app)/brain/page.tsx` — Mobile-responsive sidebar (overlay mode), responsive padding/spacing throughout, viewport detection\n- `app/globals.css` — Added mobile-specific styles (overflow, scrollbar, touch)\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- The mobile breakpoint is `md:` (768px) — below this width, the sidebar is hidden and the bottom nav appears\n- The \"More\" drawer in the bottom nav uses a slide-up panel with a 4-column grid of additional navigation items\n- The Brain chat session sidebar on mobile slides in from the left with a backdrop overlay, and auto-closes when selecting a session\n- Safe area handling is included for notched devices (`env(safe-area-inset-bottom)`)\n- TypeScript compilation passes cleanly with no errors"
}